+### Durable Tool Batches
+
+Read `session.deferredBatch` for the complete neutral snapshot of active deferred work. A durable Waiting State is settled: `isStreaming` is false, `isIdle` is true, and `waitForIdle()` resolves while `deferredBatch` remains defined.
+
+```typescript
+const snapshot = session.deferredBatch;
+if (snapshot?.kind === "batch" && snapshot.availability.status === "available") {
+  const result = await session.resumeDeferred();
+  console.log(result.status, result.deferredBatch);
+}
+```
+
+`resumeDeferred()` and `abandonDeferred()` accept no arguments and return `none`, `still_deferred`, `unavailable`, or `advanced` plus the final snapshot. A package records its typed Response before resume or typed Cancellation before abandon. A normal `prompt()` while deferred performs the ordered Interruption path; `steer()` and `followUp()` reject with `AgentSessionError.code === "agent_waiting"`.
+
+Subscribe to `deferred_batch_changed` for complete replacement snapshots, and read the getter immediately after creating/replacing a runtime for initial state. Current registration, schemas, enablement, and gates are rechecked on every advancement. See [Durable Tool Deferral](deferred-tools.md).
