+### Downstream durable-deferral format
+
+A session that first records durable deferred work is changed to the fail-closed downstream header type `dev.taylorrowser.pi-wait-for-user/session`, downstream format version `1`, with `basedOnPiSessionVersion: 3`. This namespace prevents unpatched Pi or a future official schema from silently interpreting experimental records.
+
+```json
+{"type":"dev.taylorrowser.pi-wait-for-user/session","version":1,"basedOnPiSessionVersion":3,"id":"uuid","timestamp":"...","cwd":"/path/to/project"}
+```
+
+Unsupported downstream versions or mismatched base Pi versions are rejected before mutation. Durable deferral is unavailable for in-memory sessions and `--no-session`. See [Durable Tool Deferral](deferred-tools.md).
